article.headline: Northern Arizona 97, California Maritime 47
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Steve Sir made six 3-pointers for a season-high 18 points, leading five Northern Arizona double-figure scorers in a 97-47 rout of California Maritime on Tuesday night. Ruben Boykin Jr. had 16 points and seven rebounds, Tyrone Bazy scored 14 points and reserves Riley Van Patten and Will Hensley contributed 11 and 10, respectively, to help the Lumberjacks (3-2) snap Maritime's four-game winning streak. Joel Henning scored 23 points on 9-of-17 shooting for the Keelhaulers (4-3) of the NAIA Division II California Pacific Conference. Sir, who was 6-of-7, made consecutive 3-pointers in the Lumberjacks' first two possessions, and Kyle Landry scored in transition for an 8-0 lead 1:58 into the game. Northern Arizona built the lead to 21-7 before the Keelhaulers' Tom Kreta made a 3-pointer from the left wing with 13:00 left in the first half. But the Lumberjacks answered with a 15-3 run to go ahead 36-13 over the next four minutes, was up 50-27 at halftime and kept the momentum.
